https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500null Roaming the streets of NYC, Harold vows to find a woman, someone to spend the remainder of his life with. What he finds is a beautiful transsexual woman looking for the same. Their chance meeting is not meant to be, yet a gentle knocking at her front door one evening is the catalyst for a relationship unexpected by both. All served up beneath a simply luscious jazz soundtrack. Don't Go To Strangers
